1
00:00:13,723 --> 00:00:14,853
<i>Mako!</i>

2
00:00:15,558 --> 00:00:18,842
<i>In the confusion following
the great earthquake of 1923,</i>

3
00:00:19,020 --> 00:00:22,888
<i>the anarchist Sakae Ôsugi was
assassinated, along with his wife.</i>

4
00:00:23,107 --> 00:00:25,808
<i>She was your mother, Noe Itô, right?</i>

5
00:00:27,372 --> 00:00:30,156
<i>You were seven years old
when your mother was killed.</i>

6
00:00:30,448 --> 00:00:32,387
<i>Tell me what you remember.</i>

7
00:00:33,451 --> 00:00:35,859
<i>You were seven,
so you must remember something.</i>

8
00:00:38,289 --> 00:00:42,126
<i>When your mother left that morning,
what did she say to you?</i>

9
00:00:47,298 --> 00:00:49,342
<i>Was your mother beautiful?</i>

10
00:00:50,926 --> 00:00:52,772
<i>Did you love your mother?</i>

11
00:00:55,348 --> 00:00:57,318
<i>Did you love your mother?</i>

12
00:01:10,488 --> 00:01:14,805
<i>I've wanted to meet you and
ask you these questions for a long time.</i>

13
00:01:15,128 --> 00:01:18,172
<i>Since I left Tokyo,
I've been repeating them out loud.</i>

14
00:01:19,403 --> 00:01:21,905
<i>Weren't you jealous of Noe?</i>

15
00:01:22,291 --> 00:01:24,137
<i>I mean, as a woman.</i>

16
00:01:28,474 --> 00:01:32,343
<i>All of a sudden, that day when
your parents disappeared from you,</i>

17
00:01:32,791 --> 00:01:34,783
<i>you became jealous, right?</i>

18
00:01:35,367 --> 00:01:36,795
<i>Yes, jealous...</i>

19
00:02:11,632 --> 00:02:15,303
<i>During the 28 years of her short life,
she was married three times.</i>

20
00:02:15,636 --> 00:02:18,639
<i>She left her second husband,
the poet Jun Tsuji,</i>

21
00:02:18,806 --> 00:02:22,445
<i>with whom she had two children,
in order to be with Sakae Ôsugi.</i>

22
00:02:22,737 --> 00:02:27,669
<i>She was responsible when Ôsugi's lover
Itsuko Masaoka stabbed him out of jealousy.</i>

23
00:02:27,805 --> 00:02:30,610
<i>The case of "Hikage no Chaya" in 1916.</i>

24
00:02:31,235 --> 00:02:33,998
<i>She joined the "Seitô" movement,
led by Aichô Hiraga,</i>

25
00:02:34,113 --> 00:02:36,616
<i>becoming the youngest member of the group.</i>

26
00:02:36,907 --> 00:02:40,474
<i>As the last remaining member,
she ended the movement.</i>

27
00:02:41,495 --> 00:02:46,000
<i>During the last ten years of her life,
she gave birth to seven children.</i>

28
00:02:47,043 --> 00:02:52,246
<i>In a few years, she lived as much as
the entire lives of several ordinary women.</i>

29
00:02:52,903 --> 00:02:54,206
<i>Noe Itô...</i>

30
00:02:55,249 --> 00:02:57,251
<i>was your mother, wasn't she?</i>

31
00:03:22,078 --> 00:03:24,789
Thank you. I have no more questions.

32
00:03:25,206 --> 00:03:27,041
Tell me your name once more.

33
00:03:27,792 --> 00:03:28,783
A-ko.

34
00:03:29,179 --> 00:03:30,295
But I'm Eiko.

35
00:03:30,378 --> 00:03:32,411
Eiko Sokutai, 20 year old student.

36
00:03:34,632 --> 00:03:36,998
- Then, I'm B-ko.
- Good, B-ko.

37
00:03:37,343 --> 00:03:38,928
A final word, please.

38
00:03:43,505 --> 00:03:45,601
I have nothing to do with this.

39
00:03:46,884 --> 00:03:48,761
You speak of my mother?

40
00:03:48,938 --> 00:03:50,252
I have no mother.

41
00:03:53,025 --> 00:03:55,486
You speak of my mother's mother?

42
00:03:56,675 --> 00:03:58,614
My mother has no mother.

43
00:04:00,741 --> 00:04:03,911
You speak of my mother's mother's mother?

44
00:04:05,955 --> 00:04:06,956
Then...

45
00:04:12,336 --> 00:04:13,337
It's you.

46
00:04:16,820 --> 00:04:19,204
<i>Spring, March, survivors of the massacre,</i>

47
00:04:19,205 --> 00:04:21,569
<i>We dance among the flowers</i>
- Sakae Ôsugi

48
00:04:21,570 --> 00:04:25,253
Drunk upon the happiness of decadence,
this film is a dialogue with you and I,

49
00:04:25,254 --> 00:04:29,258
the ambiguous participants in the erotica
and revolutions of Sakae Ôsugi and Noe Itô,

50
00:04:29,259 --> 00:04:31,814
whose lives were dedicated
to the beauty of chaos.

